{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.6",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 6 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:2",
      "text": "“O that my vexation were weighed, and all my calamity laid in the balances!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:3",
      "text": "For then it would be heavier than the sand of the sea; therefore my words have been rash.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:4",
      "text": "For the arrows of the Almighty are in me; my spirit drinks their poison; the terrors of God are arrayed against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:5",
      "text": "Does the wild ass bray when he has grass, or the ox low over his fodder?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:6",
      "text": "Can that which is tasteless be eaten without salt, or is there any taste in the slime of the purslane?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:7",
      "text": "My appetite refuses to touch them; they are as food that is loathsome to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:8",
      "text": "“O that I might have my request, and that God would grant my desire;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:9",
      "text": "that it would please God to crush me, that he would let loose his hand and cut me off!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:10",
      "text": "This would be my consolation; I would even exult in pain unsparing; for I have not denied the words of the Holy One.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:11",
      "text": "What is my strength, that I should wait? And what is my end, that I should be patient?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:12",
      "text": "Is my strength the strength of stones, or is my flesh bronze?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:13",
      "text": "In truth I have no help in me, and any resource is driven from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:14",
      "text": "“He who withholds kindness from a friend forsakes the fear of the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:15",
      "text": "My brethren are treacherous as a torrent-bed, as freshets that pass away,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:16",
      "text": "which are dark with ice, and where the snow hides itself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:17",
      "text": "In time of heat they disappear; when it is hot, they vanish from their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:18",
      "text": "The caravans turn aside from their course; they go up into the waste, and perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:19",
      "text": "The caravans of Tema look, the travelers of Sheba hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:20",
      "text": "They are disappointed because they were confident; they come thither and are confounded.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:21",
      "text": "Such you have now become to me; you see my calamity, and are afraid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:22",
      "text": "Have I said, ‘Make me a gift’? Or, ‘From your wealth offer a bribe for me’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:23",
      "text": "Or, ‘Deliver me from the adversary's hand’? Or, ‘Ransom me from the hand of oppressors’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:24",
      "text": "“Teach me, and I will be silent; make me understand how I have erred.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:25",
      "text": "How forceful are honest words! But what does reproof from you reprove?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:26",
      "text": "Do you think that you can reprove words, when the speech of a despairing man is wind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:27",
      "text": "You would even cast lots over the fatherless, and bargain over your friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:28",
      "text": "“But now, be pleased to look at me; for I will not lie to your face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:29",
      "text": "Turn, I pray, let no wrong be done. Turn now, my vindication is at stake.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.6.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:30",
      "text": "Is there any wrong on my tongue? Cannot my taste discern calamity?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
